# Public vs Private rule boundary

Maintain rules in three layers so the repo stays useful to the public while preserving private operator context.

## Layer 1: Public baseline (tracked)

- Keep shared engineering behavior in tracked `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files.
- **BimRoss multi-root workspaces:** company-wide rules live in the **`cursor-rules`** repo; individual repos may add their own **`.cursor/rules/`** for repo-only scope—see **`bimross-workspace-repo-rule-layering.mdc`**.
- Write guidance so an external engineer can use it without internal company access.
- Prefer generic naming for private systems unless the reference is already intentionally public.

## Layer 2: BimRoss conventions (tracked, sanitized)

- BimRoss workflow patterns are allowed in tracked rules when they are operationally useful and non-secret.
- Never include credentials, private URLs, account IDs, or sensitive customer data.
- If a BimRoss rule needs sensitive context, split it: keep the reusable policy tracked, move sensitive details to private files.

## Layer 3: Us/private business context (gitignored)

- Put private business strategy, org details, customer specifics, and internal playbooks under gitignored paths:
  - `.cursor/rules/local-context.mdc`
  - `.cursor/rules/private/**`
  - (Deprecated path, still ignored if present: `.cursor/businesses/**`—prefer `private/` or sections inside `local-context.mdc`.)
- Treat these files as local overlays on top of public rules.

### If private files were accidentally tracked

- Immediately sanitize tracked content in the repo.
- Move full private details to gitignored files.
- Remove tracked private files from git index on the next commit (`git rm --cached <path>`), keeping local copies intact.
- Keep a safe public template/example in-repo for onboarding.

## Authoring protocol

- Start with the most public-safe reusable rule first.
- Add private overlays only when needed for execution quality.
- Before commit, run a private-data scrub pass and move sensitive lines out of tracked files.
- When in doubt, default to private and then promote a sanitized version into tracked rules.
